Traced the logic on paper. Understood the O(1) time and space math trick for finding the min/max value of a stack at a given time.


Min Stack

Encoding while pushing

if(val<minVal)
{
long long flag=2LL*(val)-minVal 
st.push(flag);
minVal=val;
}


Decoding while Popping

if(st.top()<minVal)
{
long long oldMin=2*(minVal)-st.top();
minVal=oldMin;
st.pop();
}


Max Stack 

Encoding while pushing

if(val>maxVal)
{
long long flag=2*(val)-maxVal;
maxVal=val;
st.push(flag);
}

Decoding while popping

if(st.top()>maxVal)
{
long long oldMax=2*(maxVal)-st.top();
maxVal=oldMax;
st.pop();
}
